es-his-hilarious-archive-to-the-national-comedy-center-180988741/</guid></item><item><title>在白令海峡修建大坝能否使地球免受气候变化的影响？</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/could-building-a-dam-across-the-bering-straight-save-the-planet-from-some-effects-of-climate-change-180988725/</link><description>一项初步研究表明，封锁俄罗斯和阿拉斯加之间的水道可能有助于关键洋流系统的生存。但可能会产生潜在的不可预见的后果，特别是对海洋生态系统</description><pubDate>Thu, 14 May 2026 16:05:41 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/could-building-a-dam-across-the-bering-straight-save-the-planet-from-some-effects-of-climate-change-180988725/</guid></item><item><title>新研究表明，胎儿在子宫内就可以从母亲那里“感染”哈欠</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/fetuses-can-catch-yawns-from-their-mothers-while-still-in-the-womb-new-research-suggests-180988735/</link><description>打哈欠被认为是一种社交行为。虽然众所周知胎儿会打哈欠，但科学家们不确定这是否是一种独立的反射，或者他们是否能以某种方式检测到来自母亲的暗示</description><pubDate>Thu, 14 May 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/fetuses-can-catch-yawns-from-their-mothers-while-still-in-the-womb-new-research-suggests-180988735/</guid></item><item><title>智人真的比尼安德特人聪明吗？新研究表明，不同的头骨形状并不一定意味着不同的大脑容量</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/did-homo-sapiens-really-outsmart-neanderthals-different-skull-shapes-didnt-necessarily-mean-unequal-brain-capacity-new-research-shows-180988738/</link><description>美国和中国研究人员的一项研究表明，尼安德特人和早期现代人类可能具有相似的认知能力</description><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 21:29:42 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/did-homo-sapiens-really-outsmart-neanderthals-different-skull-shapes-didnt-necessarily-mean-unequal-brain-capacity-new-research-shows-180988738/</guid></item><item><title>新研究表明，经常听歌或画画放松实际上可能会延缓细胞衰老</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-relaxation-of-listening-to-a-song-or-drawing-a-picture-may-actually-slow-cellular-aging-new-research-show-180988734/</link><description>根据一项新的研究，每周接触艺术的人比每年只接触一次或两次艺术的人“生理上”年轻一岁左右</description><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 20:39:43 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-relaxation-of-listening-to-a-song-or-drawing-a-picture-may-actually-slow-cellular-aging-new-research-show-180988734/</guid></item><item><title>这幅文艺复兴时期的画作蜿蜒曲折，从希特勒的慕尼黑公寓到美国记者的家，再到伦敦国家美术馆</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-renaissance-painting-took-a-winding-path-from-hitlers-munich-apartment-to-an-american-journalists-home-to-the-national-gallery-in-london-180988733/</link><description>一位艺术历史学家最近在希特勒旧公寓的一张罕见照片中发现了 16 世纪的艺术品，该照片印在 1978 年的家具目录中</description><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 19:08:49 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-renaissance-painting-took-a-winding-path-from-hitlers-munich-apartment-to-an-american-journalists-home-to-the-national-gallery-in-london-180988733/</guid></item><item><title>这种微小的真菌在美国宇航局的灭菌协议中幸存下来，并且有可能足以污染火星</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-microscopic-fungus-survived-nasas-sterilization-protocols-and-is-hardy-enough-to-potentially-contaminate-mars-180988728/</link><description>这些微生物是从该机构的洁净室中收集的，专家们在洁净室中精心控制的环境中建造航天器。调查结果揭示了该机构在防止长期搭便车者方面的程序存在缺陷</description><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 18:57:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-microscopic-fungus-survived-nasas-sterilization-protocols-and-is-hardy-enough-to-potentially-contaminate-mars-180988728/</guid></item><item><title>观看 17 张复杂的显微镜照片，让微型世界变得无比巨大。他们赢得了年度最佳形象大赛</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-17-intricate-microscope-photographs-that-make-the-miniature-world-immense-they-won-the-evident-image-of-the-year-contest-180988722/</link><description>第六届年度竞赛展示了科学显微成像，照亮了自然界的微小部分，从单个细胞到节肢动物、硅藻和斑马鱼大脑</description><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 18:45:07 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-17-intricate-microscope-photographs-that-make-the-miniature-world-immense-they-won-the-evident-image-of-the-year-contest-180988722/</guid></item><item><title>这些海藻在海浪扰动时会发光。他们的生物发光可以为未来的无电灯供电</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-marine-algae-glow-when-waves-disturb-them-their-bioluminescence-could-power-electricity-free-lamps-of-the-future-180988721/</link><description>这些单细胞生物通常只会闪烁几毫秒，但研究人员找到了维持其发光的方法。这项技术有一天可以用来照亮机器人在深海或太空中的道路</description><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 15:43:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-marine-algae-glow-when-waves-disturb-them-their-bioluminescence-could-power-electricity-free-lamps-of-the-future-180988721/</guid></item><item><title>新数据显示，密歇根州罗亚尔岛国家公园的狼群数量激增，数量达到近 50 年来的最高水平</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/wolves-are-thriving-at-michigans-isle-royale-national-park-reaching-their-highest-numbers-in-almost-50-years-new-data-suggests-180988727/</link><description>科学家估计，目前有 37 只驼鹿在崎岖的群岛上漫步，这导致了驼鹿数量的减少。但捕食者与猎物的比例可能会趋于稳定</description><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/wolves-are-thriving-at-michigans-isle-royale-national-park-reaching-their-highest-numbers-in-almost-50-years-new-data-suggests-180988727/</guid></item><item><title>马铃薯不仅为安第斯山脉的古代土著社区提供食物，美味的块茎还重塑了人们的 DNA</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/potatoes-didnt-just-feed-ancient-indigenous-communities-in-the-andes-the-tasty-tubers-also-reshaped-peoples-dna-180988732/</link><description>一项新的研究发现，居住在现在秘鲁境内的安第斯土著人有一个名为 AMY1 的基因的额外副本，该基因有助于身体消化淀粉</description><pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 21:13:28 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/potatoes-didnt-just-feed-ancient-indigenous-communities-in-the-andes-the-tasty-tubers-also-reshaped-peoples-dna-180988732/</guid></item><item><title>NASA 刚刚上传了 Artemis 2 任务的 12,000 多张令人惊叹的照片。这是我们最喜欢的一些</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/nasa-just-uploaded-more-than-12000-stunning-photos-from-the-artemis-2-mission-here-are-a-few-of-our-favorites-180988697/</link><description>尽管此次任务的四名宇航员在太空中向地球发送了一些照片，但大多数照片在返回地球后都需要通过物理存储卡传送</description><pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 20:32:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/nasa-just-uploaded-more-than-12000-stunning-photos-from-the-artemis-2-mission-here-are-a-few-of-our-favorites-180988697/</guid></item><item><title>玛丽莲·梦露 (Marilyn Monroe) 100 岁生日系列汇集了好莱坞魅力，展现这位明星人性的一面</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/marilyn-monroe-collections-assembled-for-her-100th-birthday-cut-through-hollywood-glamour-to-reveal-the-stars-human-side-180988726/</link><description>这位电影明星的精选服装、珠宝和深色私人信件将被拍卖，以庆祝她的生日</description><pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 20:00:41 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/marilyn-monroe-collections-assembled-for-her-100th-birthday-cut-through-hollywood-glamour-to-reveal-the-stars-human-side-180988726/</guid></item><item><title>微塑料在大气中盘旋，它们可能会导致气候变化</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/microplastics-are-swirling-around-in-the-atmosphere-where-they-might-be-contributing-to-climate-change-180988704/</link><description>一项新的研究表明，空气中的塑料颗粒，尤其是彩色颗粒，吸收的阳光多于反射的阳光，从而加热周围的空气</description><pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 16:49:45 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/microplastics-are-swirling-around-in-the-atmosphere-where-they-might-be-contributing-to-climate-change-180988704/</guid></item><item><title>本杰明·富兰克林在这枚他委托纪念独立战争中的美国和法国盟友的奖章中设计了自由女神像</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/benjamin-franklin-styled-lady-libertys-look-in-this-medal-he-commissioned-to-honor-american-and-french-allies-in-the-revolutionary-war-180988723/</link><description>富兰克林将艺术与外交结合起来，创造了美国自由主义。为纪念美国成立 250 周年，巴黎造币厂对设计进行了更新</description><pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 16:03:53 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/benjamin-franklin-styled-lady-libertys-look-in-this-medal-he-commissioned-to-honor-american-and-french-allies-in-the-revolutionary-war-180988723/</guid></item><item><title>英国国王铸造这些硬币是为了抵御维京人的入侵。相反，航海袭击者将便士变成了珠宝</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/an-english-king-minted-these-coins-to-ward-off-a-viking-invasion-instead-the-seafaring-raiders-turned-the-pennies-into-jewelry-180988716/</link><description>不准备者埃塞尔雷德将对其王国的攻击视为神圣的报应。他希望公开忏悔的表现，包括制作带有宗教图像的硬币，将有助于赢得上帝的宽恕</description><pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 11:30:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/an-english-king-minted-these-coins-to-ward-off-a-viking-invasion-instead-the-seafaring-raiders-turned-the-pennies-into-jewelry-180988716/</guid></item><item><title>新线索有助于解开英国著名艺术家肖像画中被奴役男孩的谜团</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/new-clues-help-solve-the-mystery-of-an-enslaved-boy-pictured-in-a-portrait-by-a-leading-english-artist-180988717/</link><description>约书亚·雷诺兹 (Joshua Reynolds) 创作的一幅油画描绘了一名海军军官和一名黑人儿童，直到研究人员搜索了船长的日志、信件和海军部记录后，他们的人生故事才被知晓。</description><pubDate>Mon, 11 May 2026 21:57:18 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/new-clues-help-solve-the-mystery-of-an-enslaved-boy-pictured-in-a-portrait-by-a-leading-english-artist-180988717/</guid></item><item><title>这些唱歌的老鼠来回吱吱叫，而且不会中断。科学家发现了他们令人印象深刻的歌曲背后的大脑通路</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-singing-mice-squeak-back-and-forth-and-dont-interrupt-scientists-found-the-brain-pathway-behind-their-impressive-songs-180988720/</link><description>阿尔斯通的唱歌小鼠可以发出复杂​​的声音，甚至看起来可以互相礼貌地交谈。使这成为可能的神经回路比研究人员预期的要简单</description><pubDate>Mon, 11 May 2026 20:44:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-singing-mice-squeak-back-and-forth-and-dont-interrupt-scientists-found-the-brain-pathway-behind-their-impressive-songs-180988720/</guid></item></channel></rss>